orge_metadata.py:176:HUMAN_INTERVENTION_LOGS_DIRNAME = \"human-intervention-logs\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1836:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1866:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1878:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1908:            reason=\"job_failed\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2012:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2031:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2186:        \"- Include the preserved work branch URL when it is available.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2314:    if candidate.reason in {\"test_generation_failed\", \"job_failed\"}:\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2683:            reason=\"job_failed\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4782:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:21:2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:33:   dynamic-access coverage of already-supported libraries.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:222:  generation driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:237:  additional tests to improve dynamic-access coverage on an existing library\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
